    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I don't have anything against this feature but it is causing significant issues and preventing us from implementing solutions that are trivial CSS fixes (e.g. something like [this](https://github.com/ipython/ipython/compare/master...rsmith31415:css-fix-width-images)  as a fix to #7701).\n\nFurthermore, the current jquery-ui `.resizer` is not responsive-friendly, so we can't have a fully responsive (or even fluid) layout. That is by far the more important consideration in terms of user experience and as a foundation to prevent more related issues.\n\nFinally, the resizer (I think) is not widely used or even easily recognized. Its removal is not likely to disrupt the workflow of users. Actually, I would worry about excessively using the resizer to obtain larger images instead of doing it programmatically.\n"
  },
